## Miscellaneous files

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Filename                        Size    Description
------------------------------- ------- -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[alldata.zip]                      360k This file contains the data needed by
                                        the Allegro demo game. It's only needed
                                        if you got an old WIP version of the
                                        library, or if you updated to the
                                        current version via diffs, as these
                                        didn't include the demo data to save
                                        space.

[dx70_min.zip]                     440k You may have problems compiling the
                                        Allegro DLL if you don't have the
                                        correct version of the DirectX SDK
                                        library and header files. This file
                                        contains the minimal version of the
                                        DirectX 7 SDK needed to compile the DLL
                                        yourself.
                                        **Only for Windows.**

[dx70_mgw.zip]                     243k This file contains the minimal version
                                        of the DirectX 7 SDK for MinGW.
                                        **Only for Windows.**

[dx80_mgw.zip]                     442k This file contains the minimal version
                                        of the DirectX 8 SDK for MinGW.
                                        **Only for Windows.**

[dx70_dmc.zip]                     234k This file contains the minimal version
                                        of the DirectX 7 SDK for Digital Mars
                                        C/C++.
                                        **Only for Windows.**

[dx9mgw.zip]                      4180k This file contains necessary DirectX
                                        files for compiling Allegro 5.
                                         **Only for Windows.**

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

[alldata.zip]:  https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/alldata.zip
[dx70_min.zip]: https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/dx70_min.zip
[dx70_mgw.zip]: https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/dx70_mgw.zip
[dx80_mgw.zip]: https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/dx80_mgw.zip
[dx70_dmc.zip]: https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/dx70_dmc.zip
[dx9mgw.zip]:   https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/dx9mgw.zip


## Ancient versions

These files are being made available for historical interest, and as reference
material. They are unsupported, and for any serious programming work, you
should get the most recent version instead.

[Allegro 1.02](https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/allegro1.zip) (119k) - Sometime in 1995.

[Allegro 2.0](https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/alleg20.zip) (304k) - March 1996.

[Allegro 2.1](https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/alleg21.zip) (562k) - June 1996.

[Allegro 2.11](https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/alleg211.zip) (563k) - November 1996.

[Allegro 2.2](https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/alleg22.zip) (990k) - February 1997.

[Allegro 3.0](https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/alleg30.zip) (1225k) - December 1997.

[Allegro 3.1](https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/alleg31.zip) (1422k) - January 1999.

[Allegro 3.11](https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/alleg311.zip) (1434k) - February 1999.
[Patch](https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/al312dif.zip) to upgrade to version 3.12.

[Allegro 3.12](https://download.tuxfamily.org/allegro/files/alleg312.zip) (1434k) - August 1999.
This is a DOS/DJGPP library, and can be obtained from your [local Simtel
mirror](mirrors.html#simtel), in the directory gnu/djgpp/v2tk/allegro/,
filename alleg312.zip.
